"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-03-14-2024-olympic-qualifier-banyana-coach-unveils-preliminary-squad-for-falcons-showdown\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Banyana Banyana head coach Desiree Ellis has announced a 29-player squad for the team's 2024 Olympic Games final qualifying round fixture against the Super Falcons of Nigeria.  The African champions will open camp for the two fixtures on Monday, March 25.  The squad will be pared down to 23 players later this month.  Nigeria will host the first leg at the Moshood Abiola Stadium, Abuja, on Friday, April 5.  The venue for the reverse fixture will be announced in the coming days by the South Africa Football Association, SAFA.  The overall winners will earn a berth at the Paris 2024 Olympic Games.  France coach Deschamps reveals Pogba's next move after four-year ban  Ikhenoba blames loss of concentration for Bendel Insurance loss to Akwa United  WAFCON: We have not received Tinubu's $100k gift - Falcons captain, Ajibade  My Ballon d'Or nomination win for Africa - Falcons Coach, Madugu  Abia has discovered future Falcons, athletes for Nigerian - Otti  WAFCON 2024: How Banyana can beat Super Falcons - Dlamini  WAFCON 2024: We have plans for Super Falcons clash - South Africa coach Desiree Ellis  Paris 2024 qualifier: Ellis disappointed with Banyana's failure to qualify for Olympics  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"